{{Quote|Few men deserve a brutal end at an assassin's hands, but many such deserving individuals can be found in Redesign.|[[Dengar/Legends|Dengar]]|<ref name="Payback: The Tale of Dengar">{{StoryCite|story=Payback: The Tale of Dengar|book=Tales of the Bounty Hunters}}</ref>}}
'''Redesign''' was an [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] procedure that would surgically remove the parts of the brain responsible for pity and other "weak" emotions. The process was used on pacifist species to make them more aggressive, turning them into brutal savages to serve the [[New Order/Legends|New Order]]. It had also been used previously on [[Dengar/Legends|Dengar]] to make him an Imperial assassin, explaining his animus for it further.

[[Commission for the Preservation of the New Order/Legends|COMPNOR]] was responsible for the "processional orientation experiments" on planets such as [[Aruza/Legends|Aruza]]. It was here that the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] Dengar saved [[Manaroo/Legends|Manaroo]] from the operation, which he received at a younger age.

